# datahub-integrations-service Rules

## Standard Commands (run when explicitly asked)

ALWAYS run commands from the datahub-integrations-service directory with venv activated.
Use this command pattern: cd <to-datahub-integrations-service> && source venv/bin/activate && <command>

These match the CI/build configuration in build.gradle:

- Testing: pytest
- Formatting: ruff format src/ tests/ scripts/ --exclude=scripts/forms
- Linting: ruff check src/ tests/ scripts/ --exclude=scripts/forms
- Type checking: mypy --config-file=mypy.ini src/ tests/

The build also runs `../gradlew :datahub-integrations-service:lint` which runs all three tools.

## Code Conventions (MUST FOLLOW)
- Use loguru for logging. NEVER use print statements.
- Imports go at the top of the file. Only exception: circular dependencies.
- All methods MUST have type annotations. Use Pydantic and dataclasses.
- Code should be self-documenting. NEVER write module-level docstrings.
- Use # comments only for tricky details or edge cases.
- If you find yourself copying code, refactor instead.

## Testing Rules (MUST FOLLOW)
- Use pytest for testing. Prefer pytest-style tests over unittest.
- Test functions should NOT have docstrings - the test name should be clear enough.
- Comments in tests are ok to explain tricky details.
- Focus on testing core functionality and important edge cases.
- Good code is easy to test - if tests are super complex or require tons of mocks, the code is not well-designed.

## Architecture Patterns
- Extract platform-specific logic from core business logic.
- Design APIs that are stateless from the caller's perspective.
- Use context managers for temporary state or configuration.
- Prefer composition over inheritance for complex behaviors.
- Avoid superfluous state - pay careful attention to data structures and their lifecycle.

## Refactoring Guidelines
- Make minimal changes that solve the immediate problem.
- Don't remove functionality without understanding why it exists.
- Before simplifying complex logic, investigate the edge cases it handles.
- Prefer multiple small, reviewable changes over large rewrites.

## Development Commands Reference
- Setup: ../gradlew installDev && source venv/bin/activate
- Update deps: ./scripts/lockfile.sh
- Run service: uvicorn datahub_integrations.server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 9003 --reload

